---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — SoNoted"
  description="How SoNoted collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="content">
      <h1 class="title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Effective date: March 24, 2026</p>

      <p>
        SoNoted (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) operates the marketing
        site at sonoted.ai. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and
        your rights regarding that information.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what is necessary to operate this site.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Email address.</strong> When you submit the early access form, we store your email
          address on our waitlist. We use it to contact you about early access and product updates.
          We do not send marketing email to anyone who has not opted in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>IP address.</strong> Your IP address is used to enforce rate limits on form
          submissions (maximum 3 per hour per IP). It is held in memory for up to one hour and is
          never written to a database or log file.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use cookies, tracking pixels, browser fingerprinting, or third-party analytics on
        this site.
      </p>

      <h2>Sub-processors</h2>
      <p>We rely on the following third parties to operate this site:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Resend</strong> (resend.com) &mdash; transactional email delivery. Your email
          address is transmitted to Resend when you join the waitlist. Resend&rsquo;s privacy policy
          is available at resend.com/legal/privacy-policy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Railway</strong> (railway.app) &mdash; cloud hosting and infrastructure. All
          server-side processing occurs on Railway. Railway&rsquo;s privacy policy is available at
          railway.app/legal/privacy.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To notify you when early access is available</li>
        <li>To send occasional product updates (you can unsubscribe at any time)</li>
        <li>To prevent abuse of our invite form</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with any third party for their own marketing purposes.</p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain waitlist email addresses until you request deletion or until the waitlist is no
        longer active. IP addresses used for rate limiting are held in memory for up to one hour and
        are never persisted.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights under CCPA (California residents)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) gives you
        specific rights regarding your personal information.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to know.</strong> You may request a copy of the personal information we have
          collected about you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to delete.</strong> You may request that we delete your personal
          information. We will honor deletion requests within 45 days.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to opt out of sale.</strong> We do not sell personal information. There is
          nothing to opt out of.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to non-discrimination.</strong> We will not discriminate against you for
          exercising any of these rights.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights under GDPR (EEA and UK residents)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are located in the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, the General Data
        Protection Regulation (GDPR) gives you additional rights.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Lawful basis.</strong> We process your email address on the basis of your consent,
        given when you submit the early access form. You may withdraw consent at any time by
        contacting us.
      </p>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectify</strong> inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Erase</strong> your data (&ldquo;right to be forgotten&rdquo;)</li>
        <li><strong>Restrict</strong> or <strong>object</strong> to our processing</li>
        <li><strong>Data portability</strong> &mdash; receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>International transfers.</strong> Our infrastructure is hosted in the United States.
        If you are located in the EEA or UK, your data is transferred to and processed in the US.
        We rely on Standard Contractual Clauses where required.
      </p>
      <p>
        You have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        This site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
        information from children under 13. If you believe we have done so, contact us and we will
        delete it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will be noted by
        updating the effective date above. We will not retroactively weaken privacy protections
        without notice.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        To exercise any of your rights or to ask questions about this policy, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:privacy@sonoted.ai">privacy@sonoted.ai</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 6rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
</style>
